The paper introduces a new technique for model validation and evaluation, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The use of noise injection and label flipping to assess model relevance suggests a focus on machine learning and deep learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE). The evaluation of the technique on real-world datasets and synthetic datasets in the binary classification setting suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and data science (cs.DS).
